xQHvzSTINoXLtk3E9dPSwEE7aOdQDZa6_dMIXgUcwCLmn10eonnJrq9inU_XjEH-oqruRAVDNftRZUB-rmimmqhT3A8PJX2XfTpm5IQuUw6lvgBcUN8AM16-KY92mbTRfOPWjwcaUPrPq2aNw3ms6mQKHirbf9c1xvseFEIkRVve-HMgjcJ1wQp8mGPyKi1YkbHiM4_HLVRtiZ14DADFb-DhRUAVo6frkw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring X Window support**\\n\\nI’m trying to figure out how to set `isWindowAlphaSupported` to true without XOpenDisplay, which seems tricky if X isn’t available. Maybe on CI, Docker might have Xvfb for testing? For native tests, we might not even need a display. If it’s headless, I could check the GraphicsEnvironment. The problem is that `getAlphaVisualIDs` returns empty without a display, so `getVisualID` isn't even reached! It’s all about accessing the right instance and setting things up correctly, like using `Class.forName` to pull in the necessary class.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating dynamic loading and reflection**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to use an upstream source, but maybe it’s not necessary. Is Native Image dynamic class loading required? It seems not. For private class/method reflection metadata, the tests compile fine, and the agent creates the metadata. I think I need tests to run under native image by default. Direct reflection on a private method needs that metadata, which the agent collects. However, the image run should already have the metadata.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing file requirements**\\n\\nI need to use direct imports without any qualified names. Type annotations should be included as well. I shouldn't have any dollar signs in the file, so that’s good to keep in mind. Also, it seems I don't need to run tests before editing, but should I inspect the report? No, maybe I’ll skip that for now. My next step is to go ahead and create the file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_zgtyzBuE6VvQ9DL5wu8ImAtV|fc_071f34c8cde674100169f979911bd481a3a57f034ba577d491", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src